metadata.title: DPM/FM Dar, Moroccan FM agree to enhance cooperation in trade, investment

content.article_body: ISLAMABAD, Sept 27 (APP): Deputy Prime Minister / Foreign Minister Senator Mohammad Ishaq Dar and Foreign Minister of Morocco, Nasser Bourita on Saturday agreed to enhance cooperation in trade, investment, connectivity, and regional peace. The DPM/FM met with the Moroccan foreign minister on the sidelines of UNGA in New York, Foreign Office Spokesperson said in a press release. Both sides also reaffirmed their shared commitment to deepening Pakistan-Morocco relations and further strengthening collaboration at multilateral fora.
